TI  - PIMA Diabetes Prediction Using Machine Learning and Quantum Machine Learning Techniques
PY  - 2024
T2  - 2024 ITU Kaleidoscope: Innovation and Digital Transformation for a Sustainable World, ITU K 2024
DO  - 10.23919/ITUK62727.2024.10772814
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?eid=2-s2.0-85215300991&doi=10.23919%2fITUK62727.2024.10772814&partnerID=40&md5=4317abb72f07e92172c5cccbea423e2e
AB  - Quantum Machine Learning (QML) which is the integration of Quantum Mechanics (QM) and Machine Learning (ML), comes with immense computational capacity due to principles of superposition and entanglement. The PIMA diabetes dataset is used in this research as a test bed for comparing the results obtained from ML and QML approaches. The assessment shows that Support Vector Machine (SVM) has better results compared to Logistic Regression (LR) with an accuracy of 0.76. On the other hand, among QML algorithms; the Quantum Support Vector Classifier (QSVC) has a higher accuracy than the Variational Quantum Classifier (VQC) with 0.74. The findings of the given research imply that the use of QML methods may be valuable for further developments in diabetes prediction in the future.  © 2024 ITU.
